The paper deals with protecting the privacy of search engine users, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of word embeddings for finding semantically related and unrelated distractor query terms suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DB). The study of the risk of discovering search engine users' information intents indicates a potential connection to computer security (cs.CR).
